metadata.name: Badgirs City #29
metadata.description:
"I used to live in a small city placed at the center of Iran's plateau with the warmest summer days in the country part; spending most of my childhood with my sweet grandma at her old house. She was always keeping her eyes on me not to get heat stroke at noon playing in the yard when the sun was at its peak glowing furiously. Sundays at noon were my favorite, I used to call them “Ice cream” noons sitting beside the nicest person you could imagine and enjoying a delightful ice cream. You won't know how lovely it was to have an ice cream relaxing under the most enjoyable cold breeze of the tallest windcatcher in the city at her house. "



The Badgirs city is the first collaboration between Fleep and IceRain on Fxhash. The concept was established first with the design of a school with a feeling of safe and nostalgia reminding us of the good memories of our childhood as the grandma’s house and the windcatcher for Fleep.
A windcatcher (Badgir) is an Iranian traditional architectural element in the form of a small tower built on the roof of houses in warm locations to create passive cooling. The collection of Badgirs city is a modern recreational development of those traditional windcatchers designed by Fleep and icerain and exquisitely translated into code by Icerain.

Controls:
[1] Set the resolution to Medium Resolution
[2] Set the resolution to High Resolution

metadata.name: Chocolate fold #6
metadata.description:
Marzipan chocolate is one of my favorite treat. 

The bar is wrapped with thin foil that can be fold so easily it could be turn into some kind of random algorithm.

Go to https://www.artgorithm.com/experiment-23-chocolate-fold/ (or https://twitter.com/artgorithme) for an example of Marzipan chocolate folds that inspired this work.

A new serie of folds appears after 10 secondes.


Press
- 'p' to download a png

metadata.name: In a Moment, a Thousand Years #21
metadata.description:
Fragmented time and fractured memories.

=========

Controls:

[1] set resolution to 716 x 1024px (default)
[2] set resolution to 1433 x 2048px
[3] set resolution to 2455 x 3508px (approx. the size of A4 paper)
[4] set resolution to 3472 x 4961px (approx. the size of A3 paper)
[5] set resolution to 4911 x 7016px (approx. the size of A2 paper)

[0] set resolution to current window size

[c] capture a screenshot at rendered resolution

*The higher resolution settings (3-5) can slow down your device, especially on a low-end laptop without a dedicated GPU. Use it only to render and download a hi-res output for printing. For screen viewing [1] or [2] is recommended.



Made with cables.gl, a node-based webgl environment

XALTED 2022

metadata.name: SquarePlus #205
metadata.description:
A study of basic shapes ended up with Squares or Pluses. Each layer has a different color code along with a point-related rotation and scale which result in an elegant composition.

Press s in live mode to download.

Download a higher resolution by adding to the URL:
&density=2 / &density=3 / &density=4

Lammetje Februari 2023

metadata.name: Tangentum #8
metadata.description:
We live in a multiverse: an infinite-dimensional space of variants. Everything exists here. Everything is possible. Each subset of a multiverse has its own unique laws of physics, a set of rules, and its own distinct features.

Tangentum creates a projection of a random multiverse subset to a 2-dimensional plane. Each variation is a unique representation of the force field, that exists somewhere at some point in time.

This work starts a series of my visual exploration of functions, continuity, and boundedness, and I would love to share it with you.


Please use fullscreen or download artwork in high resolution for a better viewing experience.

Tested with Chrome 107, Safari, and Firefox. Chrome is recommended, other browsers are slower on this artwork.

Saving with high and ultra-high resolution may take a while, please be patient.


Made with love and p5js


Controls in fullscreen:
[1] - save PNG 2700 x 1800
[2] - save PNG 5400 x 3800
[3] - save PNG 10800 x 7600
[4] - save PNG 16200 x 11400

metadata.name: CMYK:Unchecked #31
metadata.description:
CMYK:Unchecked offers almost infinite canvases designed to challenge the concept and state of being unverified.

Layout variations include 80 / 40 / 20 / 10 / 5 / 4 / 1 circles. 
Each circle presented is either Cyan, Magento, Yellow or Black.

---

This work is of course a parody of 'Checks' by Jack Butcher presented in a transformative way. The work is in no way related to the original 'Checks' work and is not intended to fool anyone into thinking so thus does not affect the originals market or value.
